Prefer TypeScript for all frontend code (components, hooks, utilities, and configuration where supported).

Use Tailwind CSS as the default styling system.

Favor modern, clean, and forward-looking frontend tooling and patterns (for example: component-driven architecture, accessible UI primitives, and lightweight utility-first libraries).

Keep implementations minimal, maintainable, and visually clean by default.

Use functional React components and hooks; avoid class components.

Prefer strict TypeScript typing; avoid `any` unless there is a clear, documented reason.

Prefer utility-first styling with Tailwind classes; avoid standalone CSS files unless required for third-party integration or truly global styles.

Prioritize accessibility by default (semantic HTML, keyboard support, visible focus states, and proper ARIA usage when needed).

Prefer composable, headless, or minimally opinionated UI primitives over heavy monolithic UI frameworks.



Prefer Python for backend and postgress for database